<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870424-0078 </DOCNO><HL> Financing Business:Hard Rock Cafe PLC</HL><DD> 04/24/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> HRCSTOCK MARKET, OFFERINGS (STK)INITIAL STOCK OFFERINGS (INI) </IN><TEXT>   HARD ROCK CAFE PLC sold 2,550,000 American depositary receipts at $16 each in its inital U.S. offering, said chief underwriter Drexel Burnham Lambert Inc. An ADR represents ownership of securities that physically remain abroad. Each ADR represents five ordinary shares of the London-based operator and franchiser of Hard Rock Cafe restaurants. The company offered 2,310,000 receipts and a shareholder the rest, Drexel Burnham said. Proceeds will be used to finance additional U.S. restaurants, to expand existing restaurants, to pay debt and for general purposes, the underwriter said. In composite trading on the American Stock Exchange yesterday, Hard Rock's ADRs closed at $16.125, as 864,900 ADRs moved. </TEXT></DOC>